<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 04 at 9:43PM EST  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Scattered Snow Showers and Patchy Blowing and Drifting Snow...
Lingering snow showers may continue to cause brief, localized
bursts of heavier snow through about 930 PM. Gusty winds from the
west-northwest may cause low visibility due to patchy blowing and
drifting snow, especially in rural or open, exposed areas. Those
who are planning to drive through the late evening should leave
extra time to reach their destinations. When driving on snow
covered roads, drive slowly and increase following distance.</description>
